* 3N Opening

In 1st/2nd:

- Good 4HS opening
- P/T integrity for the 4 level
- Semi-solid+ suit
- Exactly 2 or 3 keycards (1) AK trumps (2) A or K trumps + side Ace (3) AK trumps + side ace

3N
    4C = keycard count ask, further cue bids may fish for a void
        4M = natural, 2 keycards
        4D = !hs + 3 keycards
        4N = !ss + 3 keycards
    4D = extra trump length (8 cards) ask, further cue bids may fish for a void
        4M = nope
        4oM = keycard min, 2 keycards
        4N = keycard max, 3 keycards
    4H = Pass or Correct
    4S = to play (typically knows partner's suit is !ss)
3N
    (any)
        X = penalty
        XX = penalty

In 3rd/4th:

- Generic to play opening

